definition.value: An amino acid zwitterion of L-homocitrulline arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-hydroxyphenylacetic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfate oxoanion that is a trianion arising from deprotonation of the O-sulfo, N-sulfo and carboxy groups of 3-D-glucuronosyl-N(2),6-disulfo-beta-D-glucosamine; major species at pH 7.3.
Tetraanion of methanofuran arising from deprotonation of all five carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of cis-4-coumaric acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A UDP-rhamnose(2-) species in which the rhamnose portion has L-configuration; the major form of UDP-L-rhamnose at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of N-(2,3-dihydroxybenzoyl)-L-serine; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of N-methyltyramine; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of N-adenylylanthranilic acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphoramidate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxy groups of 2-O-caffeoylglucaric acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of aminomalonic acid arising from deprotonation of the two carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of uracil-5-carboxylic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dizwitterionic form of L-cystathionine arising from transfer of two protons from the carboxy to the amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Dizwitterionic form of homocystine arising from transfer of two protons from the carboxy to the amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of (S)-atropine arising from protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 3',5'-cyclic AMP arising from deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of CDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-glucose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The ammonium betaine of a 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of 2-(alpha-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of psychosine sulfate arising from transfer of a proton from the sulfo to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 7,8-dihydroxykynurenic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of dTDP-D-fucose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of L-gamma-glutamyl-L-cysteine arising from deprotonation of both carboxy groups and protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Tricarboxylate anion of but-1-ene-1,2,4-tricarboxylic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of N-methyl-L-alanine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of phenylthioacetohydroximic acid arising from deprotonation of the acidic SH group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of testolic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
The trianion resulting from the removal of the three protons from the diphosphate group of all-trans-hexaprenyl diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A N-alkylpiperazine that is piperzine in which the nitrogens atoms are substituted by 2-(2-hydroxyethoxy)ethyl and (4-chlorophenyl)(phenyl)methyl groups respectively.
Conjugate base of L-arogenic acid arising from deprotonation of the two carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of trans-beta-D-glucosyl-2-hydroxycinnamic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of (S)-6-hydroxynicotine; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of 6-amino-2-oxohexanoic acid arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate acid of L-tyrosyl-L-arginine arising from deprotonation of the carboxy terminus and protonation of the side-chain guanidino group and the amino terminus; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is a trianion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of 2-carboxy-D-arabinitol 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group and the phosphate OH groups of 1-phospho-alpha-D-galacturonic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
The ionic polymer obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of alginic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4-sulfate arising from deprotonation of the sulfate and phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleoside 5'-diphosphate(3-) obtained by deprotonation of the three diphosphate OH groups of guanosine 5'-diphosphate (GMP); major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of O-phosphoethanolamine arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of a 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups.
Conjugate base of quercitrin arising from selective deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of 3alpha(S)-strictosidine arising from protonation of the secondary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of biochanin A arising from selective deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of S-(5-deoxy-D-ribos-5-yl)-L-homocysteine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of (3R)-3-hydroxy-L-aspartic acid arising from deprotonation of the two carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-homocysteine; major species at pH 7.3.
